[I]     Lar - I had no idea Larian was a lil company, lol, had I known, I would probibly had said nothing, I just learned of the demo 2 days ago...but aye, it always comes down to money and time, and money, and more money, did I mention the money part?  But ya, smaller groups whom have to support themselves end up lucking out even more than those that do get a publisher, those of which can lack in patience for a good game to be made right, no suprise to me there...with Larian's situation in mind, I'm astonished at what you have now.  

     Tutamon - First, thanx for the item label tip...next to macro potions and skills, it's just like in the Diablo series, put your cursor over the skill or potion you want to assign, then pick a function key and hit it, in Divine Divinity's case, your options are F1 to F6...aswell with making potions, I think it's a bug, since I don't have the problem your having, when I make a potion and pick it up off the ground, it always stacks, even with the store bought variety, regardless what type of potion...and lastly, you want stupid skeletons?...try Dungeon Seige, they make excellent archery or magery practice since if you keep at a fair stretch away, they keep retreating, returning, retreating, returning, lol, I fell off my chair laughing the first time I saw it.

